From My Little Stick of Blackpool Rock to God Save the Queen, this is the
story of ten records from the 1930s to the present day that have been banned
by the BBC. The reasons why these songs were censored reveals the changing
controversies around youth culture over the last 75 years, with Bing Crosby
and the Munchkins among the unlikely names to have met the wrath of the BBC.

With contributions from Carrie Grant, Paul Morley, Stuart Maconie,
Glen Matlock, Mike Read and Jon Robb.
